Title : Lutzelfrau
Text : '''Lutzelfrau''' is a [[witch]] in [[German folklore]] who gives gifts — particularly apples, nuts and dried plums — to children on [[Saint Lucy's Day]] (December 13).<ref name="Kretzenbacher1959" >{{cite book|title=Santa Lucia und die Lutzelfrau |last=Kretzenbacher |first=Leopold |year=1959 |publisher=R. Oldenbourg}}</ref> ''Lutzelfrau'' customs are also common in [[Slovenia]] and [[Croatia]], where a "dark Luz" was contrasted to the [[Saint Lucy|Christian saint]].<ref name="Kretzenbacher1959" /> 

